{"author":{"id":"69a73b59e8bca0653e9174a374f9f55c998c9a49750b37bad6bd3960e96b7ca3"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1717419497,"nonce":"2ecJl3Jp+sn85tlxMudFd6OkgV8=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDODBZtRc5_3EE-","github-url":"https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/1446#issuecomment-2145141054"},"message":"@yarikoptic \n\n\u003e if not a URL (ie local path) - using `glob.glob(PATH, recursive=True)` locally\n\n[As I stated above](https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/1446#issuecomment-2127372344), local (non-URL) paths passed to `dandi delete` are only matched against server paths; the only role of the local Dandiset is in ensuring the paths are relative to the Dandiset root.  If we want `dandi delete` to handle globbing of local/file/non-URL paths, shouldn't the globbing happen against server paths rather than local paths for consistency?\n\nAlso, do we want to support local path arguments that contain a glob in the Dandiset path portion, e.g., `dandi delete /home/user/00000*/*.nwb` when run inside a Dandiset at `/home/user/000001`?  That would be tricky.","files":null}]}